INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_laf4300','letter','1784-03-09','Paris','','FRA','Gilbert du Motier','Lafayette','','George','Washington','','individual','','Had I not so perfect a confidence in your friendship, I should very much fear to tire you with my scribbling of this day ; but cannot leave my pen before I have again mentioned my tender, respectful affection to my dear General.','ltr_laf4300.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_laf4301','letter','1784-08-10','Philadelphia','PA','US','Gilbert du Motier','Lafayette','','George','Washington','','individual','','I have already had the pleasure to acquaint you with my arrival in America, and am endeavouring to reach Mount Vernon as soon as possible.','ltr_laf4301.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_laf4302','letter','1784-10-08','Albany','NY','US','Gilbert du Motier','Lafayette','','George','Washington','','individual','','Everywhere I have met with delays; but so agreeable were they in their nature, that I cannot complain of them. It is not quite the same with the Indian treaty, although the hope to he useful has kept me there longer than I had expected.','ltr_laf4302.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_laf4303','letter','1784-10-22','Boston','MA','US','Gilbert du Motier','Lafayette','','George','Washington','','individual','','On my arrival at Boston, I have been so friendly received, that no words can express my truly affectionate gratitude.','ltr_laf4303.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_laf4304','letter','1784-12-21','New York','NY','US','Gilbert du Motier','Lafayette','','George','Washington','','individual','','No, my beloved General, our late parting was not by any means a last interview. My whole soul revolts at the idea ; and could I harbour it an instant, indeed, my dear General, it would make me miserable.','ltr_laf4304.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_laf4305','letter','1785-07-04','Paris','','FRA','Gilbert du Motier','Lafayette','','George','Washington','','individual','','My dear General, This letter will be delivered by the celebrated M. Houdon, who is going, for your statue, to America.','ltr_laf4305.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_laf4306','letter','1785-07-14','Sarreguemines','','FRA','Gilbert du Motier','Lafayette','','George','Washington','','individual','','I have been lately visiting some French towns, where I spoke a great deal about American trade, and fully answered the views I had the honor to communicate in a former letter.','ltr_laf4306.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_laf4307','letter','1785-09-03','Vienna','','AUT','Gilbert du Motier','Lafayette','','George','Washington','','individual','','This letter has been requested of me as an introduction for M. Andre Michaux, whom, for many reasons, I am happy to present.','ltr_laf4307.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_laf4308','letter','1786-02-10','Paris','','FRA','Gilbert du Motier','Lafayette','','George','Washington','','individual','','The inclosed, my dear General, is a vocabulary which the Empress of Russia has requested me to have filled up with Indian names, as she has ordered a universal dictionary to be made of all languages.','ltr_laf4308.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_laf4309','letter','1786-10-26','Paris','','FRA','Gilbert du Motier','Lafayette','','George','Washington','','individual','','I have been travelling through some garrison towns, in order to preserve the habit of seeing troops and their tactics. Now I am mostly at Fontainbleau, where the Court is residing for a few weeks.','ltr_laf4309.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_laf4310','letter','1787-05-05','Paris','','FRA','Gilbert du Motier','Lafayette','','George','Washington','','individual','','he persuaded the King to assemble notable persons of each order, to please them with a plan of Assemblies in each Province, which was much desired, and to get their approbation for new taxes, with which he durst not, by himself, saddle the nation.','ltr_laf4310.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_laf4311','letter','1787-10-15','Paris','','FRA','Gilbert du Motier','Lafayette','','George','Washington','','individual','','My dear General, I have a few days ago written to you by M. de Moustier, the new Minister from this Court. He is a sensible and honest man, with whom I think that the people of America will be satisfied.','ltr_laf4311.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_laf4312','letter','1788-01-01','Paris','','FRA','Gilbert du Motier','Lafayette','','George','Washington','','individual','','It is needless for me to tell you, that I read the new proposed Constitution with an unspeakable eagerness and attention. I have admired it, and find in it a bold, large, and solid frame for the Confederation.','ltr_laf4312.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_laf4313','letter','1788-05-25','Paris','','FRA','Gilbert du Motier','Lafayette','','George','Washington','','individual','','Permit me once more, my beloved General, to insist on your acceptance of the Presidency.','ltr_laf4313.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_laf4314','letter','1790-03-17','Paris','','FRA','Gilbert du Motier','Lafayette','','George','Washington','','individual','','Our revolution is getting on as well as it can, with a nation that has swallowed liberty at once, and is still liable to mistake licentiousness for freedom.','ltr_laf4314.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_laf4315','letter','1790-08-28','Paris','','FRA','Gilbert du Motier','Lafayette','','George','Washington','','individual','','For God\'s sake, my dear General, take care of your health ! Do not devote yourself so much to the Cabinet, while your habit of life has, from your young years, accustomed you to constant exercise.','ltr_laf4315.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_laf4316','letter','1791-03-07','Paris','','FRA','Gilbert du Motier','Lafayette','','George','Washington','','individual','','Whatever expectations I had conceived of a speedy termination to our revolutionary troubles, I still am tossed about in the ocean of factions and commotions of every kind.','ltr_laf4316.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_laf4317','letter','1791-05-03','Paris','','FRA','Gilbert du Motier','Lafayette','','George','Washington','','individual','','The rage of parties, even among the patriots, is gone as far as it is possible, short of bloodshed ; but, although hatreds are far from subsiding, matters do not appear so ill disposed as they formerly were towards a collision among the supporters of the popular cause.','ltr_laf4317.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_laf4318','letter','1791-06-06','Paris','','FRA','Gilbert du Motier','Lafayette','','George','Washington','','individual','','The Assembly has put an end to her existence by a new convocation ; has unfitted her own members for immediate reelection and places in the Executive; and is now reducing the Constitution to a few principal articles','ltr_laf4318.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
